Inside the Applications folder near the very bottom is the 'Utilities' folder. Open that folder. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7c/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/7/7c/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Find and double-click the 'Terminal' application with the left mouse button to open it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/a/a6/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.6666666666667,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

This is done using the 'sudo' command (Switch User and Do). In terminal type the following sudo ls (all lowercase) and hit [Return] on your keyboard. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/3/38/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.6666666666667,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Terminal will prompt you for a password Use your administrator account password. If you don't have a password, leave it blank. [NOTE: For security reasons, unlike Windows, Mac OS X won't show any sign that you are typing your password, just type normally, even though nothing shows. ]{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/77/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/7/77/Remove-.Ds_Store-Files-on-Mac-Os-X-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
